{"TopicId":218209,"ForumId":200,"TopicTitle":"Fiddling with symmetry while placing struts causes attachment noded to be left behind after deleting","CreatedByName":"Sylvi Fisthaug","CreatedById":228381,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-04T17:58:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sylvi Fisthaug","CreatedById":228381,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-04T17:58:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 22H2 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 5600X 6-Core Processor 3.70 GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A03070 TI | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32,0 GB 3600 mhz (operating at 3200 mhz) cl17\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpecs:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_07/hardware.jpg.217374273606d31b5cd883e71778988f.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#e6e8e9;font-size:15px;\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hardware.jpg.217374273606d31b5cd883e71778988f.jpg\u0022 data-ratio=\u002269.75\u0022 style=\u0022border-style:none;vertical-align:middle;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_07/hardware.jpg.217374273606d31b5cd883e71778988f.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis bug is a bit tricky to reproduce. It applies for fuel lines as well, as they are based on the same placement mechanic as struts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you end up fiddling around with the symmetry in the \u003Cs\u003Eright\u003C/s\u003E wrong way while placing them, they leave behind initial placement parts as described above.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to reproduce\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EChoose high count symmetry.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPlace struts\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EChoose lower count symmetry\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EGrab the last placed node\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPlace it again\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EPick up the last placed node again, and delete it.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe nodes left behind is still placed in original symmetry, but the symmetry does not apply anymore. As shown in the video below, they will have to be removed one by one, regardless of chosen symmetry.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThey all do disappear at launch though.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPossible fix\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224295271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217807\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687448700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210281\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Intercept Games\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/23/2023 at 3:45 AM, Intercept Games said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed: changing radial symmetry count after placing the first part of a strut causes the strut to break\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis didn\u0027t really fix the issue in my opinion, to me it appears that you are just blocked from changing symmetry while \u0022holding\u0022 a strut.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA possible fix to the bug described above, could be that you are allowed to change symmetry when selecting a strut or fuel line from the part manager, but will be blocked from changing it after placing the first node.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/bVnVaXiaW8s?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022struts bug. fiddling with symmetry\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-08T15:39:06Z\u0022 title=\u002207/08/2023 03:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 8, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}